cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.IT

The paper discusses empirical evaluation of algorithms for the multi-armed bandit problem, which is a well-known problem in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the application of bandit algorithms in clinical trials, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
